HEADWORD: tagre
<hw>⟦Eacute⟧`ta`g⟦egrave⟧re"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., fr. <ets>⟦eacute⟧tager</ets> to arrange on shelves, fr.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧tage</ets> story, floor. See <er>Stage</er>.]</ety> <def>A
piece of furniture having a number of uninclosed shelves or stages, one
above another, for receiving articles of elegance or use.</def>
<rj><au>Fairholt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

